{
  "version": "hindcast-validation-v1",
  "methodVersion": "grounded-v3",
  "comparisonType": "model present-day vs independent ERA5 reanalysis observations",
  "model": {
    "year": 2025,
    "scenario": "ssp245",
    "variable": "annual_mean_temperature_c"
  },
  "observed": {
    "source": "Open-Meteo ERA5 archive (daily temperature_2m_mean)",
    "period": "2015-2024",
    "window_center_year": 2019.5
  },
  "method": "- Model: grounded_model.project(lat, lng, 2025, ssp245).annual_mean.\n  - Observed: Open-Meteo ERA5 daily mean temperature averaged over 2015-2024\n    (a recent ~decadal normal; window center ~2019.5).\n  - Residual = model(2025) - observed(2015-2024).\n  - The model year (2025) is ~5 years AFTER the observation-window center, so a\n    correctly-anchored model should read slightly WARMER than the window\n    (~+0.1-0.2 C from trend). A NEGATIVE residual therefore indicates a cold\n    lean beyond what the time offset explains.\n  - ERA5 is ~25 km reanalysis; for a point city it can differ from a station /\n    high-res product by ~0.5 C (representativeness). Treat the per-city number\n    as indicative; the aggregate bias is the load-bearing signal.\n\nRun from repo root:  python3 scripts/hindcast_validation.py\nWrites: data/hindcast-validation.openmeteo.json",
